FBIS4-14263 "drnes083_w_94005" FBIS-NES-94-083 Daily Report 24 Apr 1994 Sri Lanka Increase in External Assets Reported Increase in External Assets Reported BK2404115994 Colombo Sri Lanka Broadcasting Corporation International Service in English 1045 GMT 24 Apr 94 BK2404115994 Colombo Sri Lanka Broadcasting Corporation International Service English BFN [Text] Sri Lanka's external assets rose substantially by $735 million. According to Central Bank statistics, the official reserve has also recorded an increase. This increase of $736 [as heard] million reflects the growing capital inflows and remittances. The country's foreign assets increased to 2,298 million rupees by the end of February this year. The remittances of foreign expatriates have also recorded an increase of 16 percent. The tourist arrivals recorded an upsurge of four percent.
